{"title_page": "Chandrashekhar (actor)", "text_new": "{{other people||Chandrasekhar (disambiguation){{!}}Chandrasekhar}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox actor\n| name               = Chandrashekhar G. Vaidya\n| native_name_lang   = Hin\n| birth_date         = 7 July 1922\n| birth_place        = Haydrabad, [[Telangana]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = Indian\n| citizenship        = Indian\n| occupation         = Actor\n| known_for          = \n| television         = Ramayan (1987)\n}}\n[[File:Bollywood Photographer Camaal Mustafa Sikander with Bollywood Actor Chandrashekhar.jpg|thumb|right|225px|Chandrashekhar (right)]]\n\n'''Chandrashekhar''', whose full name is Chandrashekhar. G. Vaidya (born 7 July 1922)<ref>{{cite news|last=IANS|title=Veteran actor Chandrashekhar turns 90!|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/veteran-actor-chandrashekhar-turns-90/|accessdate=21 November 2013|newspaper=.bollywoodlife.com|date=7 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026122435/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/veteran-actor-chandrashekhar-turns-90/|archive-date=26 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>  is an Indian [[film actor]] working in the [[Bollywood]] film industry.\n\n== Early life ==\nChandrashekhar was born in Hyderabad on July 7, 1922. He dropped out of college, and moved to Bombay in the early 1940s. He has a diploma in western dancing from the UK.{{cn}}\n\n== Film career ==\nChandrashekar, on recommendation from the singer Shamshad Begum, got his first job with Shalimar Studios in Pune in 1948. Then he got junior artiste role in  'Bebas' (1950) with Bharat Bhushan as the lead hero.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/yesteryear-actor-chandrashekhar-is-97-years-young-where-are-they-now/1589611|title=Yesteryear actor Chandrashekhar is 97 years young! (Where Are They Now?)|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nHe initially did junior artiste roles in films like Nirdoshi(1951), Farmiash (1953), Meenar (1954). He has appeared in about 250 films since his appearance in  the 1954 film ''[[Aurat Teri Yehi Kahani]]'' as an actor. His first film as hero was ''[[Surang]]'' (1953), produced by [[V. Shantaram]]. Some of his characters, as the supporting actor which became popular came in films like Gateway of India, Fashion(1957),  Barsaat Ki Ek Raat (1960), [[Baat Ek Raat Ki]], Angulimaal(1960), Rustom-E-Baghdad (1963), King Kong(1962), Jahan Ara (1964). He also produced, directed and acted in as the lead hero his hit musical film ''Cha Cha Cha'' (1964),  which was the first film of Helen as a lead heroine. ''Cha Cha Cha'' is one of the films featured in Avijit Ghosh's book; 40 Retakes: Bollywood Classics You May Have Missed. In 1966, he directed and produced his second film Street Singer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamsham.com/en/chandrashekhar-ninety-seven-and-still-cha-cha-cha|title=Chandrashekhar ninety seven and still cha cha cha|website=Glamsham|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nChandrashekhar was the leading man in films like \"Surang\" (1953), \"Kavi\" and \"Mastana\" (both 1954), \"Baradari\" (1955), ''Kali Topi Lal Rumal'' (1959), ''Street Singer'', ''Rustem-e-Bughdaad'' (with Dara Singh) and in a negative role in ''[[Basant Bahar (film)|Basant Bahar]]''.\nIt was after 1968, that Chandrashekar, was not getting offers to act as the lead hero. So he moved into character roles. He was regular character actor in directorial ventures of [[Shakti Samanta]] and films with [[Rajesh Khanna]] as the lead hero, with films like [[Kati Patang]], [[Ajnabee (1974 film)|Ajnabee]],  [[Mehbooba (1976 film)|Mehbooba]], [[Alag Alag]]. \n\nFrom 1971 onwards until 1987, he acted as the character actor in films like [[Hum Tum Aur Woh (1971 film)|Hum Tum Aur Woh]], [[Dharma]], [[Charitraheen]], [[Vardaan]], [[Ranga Khush]], [[Shakti]], [[Shankar Dada]](1976), [[Anpadh]](1978), [[Saajan Bina Suhagan]], [[Karmyogi]],  [[The Burning Train]], [[Namak Halal]], [[Nikkah]], [[Ayaash]],  [[Maan Gaye Ustaad]] (1981) [[Disco Dancer]], [[Sharaabi]], [[Sansar]]{{dn|date=April 2020}}, [[ Hukumat]] . Rajesh Khanna helped him in getting character roles in the films with Khanna in lead role like [[Dhanwan (1981 film)|Dhanwan]] (1981), [[Insaaf Main Karoonga]], [[Durgaa]],  [[Avam]], [[Sitapur Ki Geeta]] and [[Begunaah]].  He was a close friend of actors [[Pran (actor)|Pran]], [[Dara Singh]], [[Rajesh Khanna]], [[Jeevan]], [[Devanand]] and directors [[B. R. Chopra]], [[Pramod Chakravarthy]], [[Shakti Samata]] and [[Ramanand Sagar]].\n\nHe decided to work as assistant director to Gulzar at the age of 50, when he felt, he needed to do more in film industry. He assisted Gulzar in films like [[Parichay (film)|Parichay]], [[Koshish]], [[Achanak (1973 film)|Achanak]], [[Aandhi]], [[Khushboo (1975 film)|Khushboo]] and [[Mausam (1975 film)|Mausam]] between 1972 to 1976.\n\nHe also played character role of Arya Sumant as [[Dasharatha]]'s prime minister in [[Ramanand Sagar]]'s TV Series [[Ramayan (1987 TV series)|Ramayana]] at the age of 65.\n\nIn late 1988, post Ramayan, despite him being, above age of 66, he was offered roles as old man in character roles of Policeman or Father or Judge, in films like Tamacha (1988), Elaan-E-Jung, Mera Pati Sirf Mera Hai, Jawani Zindabad, Gurudev, Humshakal (1992), Waqt Ka Badshah.\n\n== Other work ==\nHe served as President of the Cine Artistes Association (CINTAA) from 1985 to 1996. He served in different capacities as President of the Federation of Western India Cine Employees, All India Film Employees Confederation, trustee of Cine Artistes Welfare Fund of India and Cine Artiste Welfare Trust, Vice-President of Indian Film Directors Association, associated as Member with Film Writers Association, Indian Motion Pictures Producers Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/aug/04/yesteryear-bollywood-actor-chandrashekhar-vaidya-is-97-years-young-2014028.html|title=Yesteryear Bollywood actor Chandrashekhar Vaidya is 97 years young!|website=The New Indian Express|accessdate=8 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806130911/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/aug/04/yesteryear-bollywood-actor-chandrashekhar-vaidya-is-97-years-young-2014028.html|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nChandrashekhar retired from the industry in 2000 after appearing in ''[[Khauff]]'' at the age of 78.\n\nChandrashekhar's son Ashok Shekhar is a known television serial producer and also runs an events and celeb management company, and his grandson [[Shakti Arora]], is an actor.<ref>{{cite news|author=Neha Maheshwri, TNN|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-19/tv/31367302_1_shakti-arora-chandrashekhar-hindi-and-urdu|title=Shakti Arora is Chandrashekhar's grandson|publisher=The Times of India|date=2012-04-19|accessdate=2013-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121204022726/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-19/tv/31367302_1_shakti-arora-chandrashekhar-hindi-and-urdu|archive-date=4 December 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/silsila-badalte-rishton-kas-shakti-arora-shares-a-picture-with-96-year-old-grandfather-and-veteran-actor-chandrashekhar/articleshow/69436455.cms|title=Silsila Badalte Rishton Ka's Shakti Arora shares a picture with 96-year-old grandfather and veteran actor Chandrashekhar - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=8 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522234422/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/silsila-badalte-rishton-kas-shakti-arora-shares-a-picture-with-96-year-old-grandfather-and-veteran-actor-chandrashekhar/articleshow/69436455.cms|archive-date=22 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0151539|name=Chandrashekhar}}\n\n\n{{authority c